text.tspan: The Managing Director, as the ERT Chairman serves as the designated spokesperson. In his absence, the Managing Director maynominate another senior manager to act on his behalf.Staff are not permitted to give any interviews or statements to the press without prior approval of the Managing Director. Howevershould there be a media inquiry to an incident every employee must know how to conduct themselves and where to direct mediainquiries. This includes not only the reception staff that is likely to receive incoming calls but all employees as they might beapproached by the media by a blind telephone call or in person at the company offices.A Sample Media Holding Statement and Press Issue Statement is enclosed in Section 7.10. Any information that will be released tothe media must be approved by the Managing Director prior to release.A pre-prepared ‘Blind Site’ with media response templates has been added to the company’s website which can be switched on whenrequired. IT support is to be contacted for this purpose. In addition the IT department will also remove all contact details and telephonenumbers of Head office and other offices from Company websites and keep only designated numbers which are to be used for mediaresponse.7.9.2PUBLIC RELATIONS/MEDIA CONSULTANTAll internal and external media/ communications requirements of the company will be handled by the Media/ Communications team.This may include communicating with media and other concerned agencies.If necessary, a dedicated extension number for the exclusive use of the Media/ Communication team, and notify the receptionistaccordingly.7.9.3RECEPTION STAFF AND MEDIAReception staff plays an important role as gatekeepers for their company. Reception staff not only provides physical security, they alsocontribute to information security. It is important that media/ communication team keep reception staff appraised of significant issuesthat may generate media interest so reception staff can be prepared for and not surprised by a large number of media calls.1. Reception staff is to contact the Director, HR & Crew on all aspects regarding interacting with the Media.2. If you are contacted via phone by a reporter, then following is the sequence of action to be taken: a. Inform the reporterQuote “I would be pleased to assist you. I’ll connect you to the concerned person”.Unquoteb. Put the call on hold. Do not send to voice mail (voice mail is sometimes ignored during a crisis event and sending a reporter’s queryto voice mail often results in the reporter’s question not being answered).c. Try to contact Director, HR & Crew, in case of her non-availability then contact the Managing Director.d. If you cannot locate or contact them then tell the caller that the spokesperson is not in the office and state that he/ she will return thecall as soon as possible.e. Thank the caller, and record the: i. Date: ii. Time: iii. Reporter’s name: iv. Phone number: v. Email: vi. Media outlet the reporter works for: vii. Reporter’s deadline (when they need an answer by): viii. Information they are looking for:f. Forward information from the caller immediately to the Director, HR & Crew or the Managing Director. as soon as possible.g. If a reporter persists in wanting you to comment, simply sayQuote“I am not the concerned person and do not have the information that you seek. I will get your request to the concerned person as soonas possible.”Unquoteh. Do not forward reporter’s calls into the company’s crisis room/ emergency operations center.i. Do not confirm that an incident has occurred.7.9.4OTHER OFFIEC STAFF (OTHER THAN RECEPTION STAFF) AND MEDIAA. Statement when in OfficeIf you are contacted via phone by a reporter, then say the following:<Quote> “I am not the concerned person. I am not in the position to answer your questions at the moment. I’ll connect you with the staff thatis handling this.”<Unquote>
